content: Drink a glass of water first thing in the morning to kickstart your metabolism and rehydrate after sleep. Add lemon for extra benefits!
Before getting out of bed, try these gentle stretches: cat-cow pose, gentle twists, and ankle rotations. It helps wake up your body naturally.
Take time to chew your food slowly and savor each bite. This not only improves digestion but also helps you feel more satisfied with smaller portions.
Avoid screens 30 minutes before bedtime. The blue light can interfere with your sleep cycle. Try reading a book instead!
Write down 3 things you're grateful for each day. This simple practice can significantly improve your mental well-being and outlook on life.
Walking Meetings - Instead of sitting in a conference room, try walking meetings. You'll get exercise, fresh air, and often more creative ideas flow when moving.
Wake up early - It keeps the mood good for the remaining day
